&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Services Assistant Manager, Quality Relations&lt;/strong&gt;, you&#39;ll be the operational engine behind our Specialist and Correspondence Specialist teams across Vendor Relations and Placements. You&#39;ll serve as the operational second-in-command to the Program Manager — keeping day-to-day execution on track, holding standards high, and making continuous improvement a way of life for your teams. This is a role for someone who thrives in complexity, communicates with clarity, and brings both analytical rigor and genuine people leadership to everything they do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Nightingale&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nightingale Education Group is more than a nursing school — we&#39;re a high-impact community on a mission to transform healthcare access through exceptional nursing education. Our collaborators don&#39;t just fill roles; they drive purpose, shape outcomes, and show up for one another every single day. If you&#39;re looking for work that genuinely matters, you&#39;ve found the right place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support program leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in overseeing Specialist and Correspondence Specialist teams, including coaching, professional development, and performance management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive operational excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;by monitoring adherence to Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) and departmental processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyze KPIs&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to identify trends, gaps, and opportunities — then translate data into actionable recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to ensure learners, faculty, and vendors receive seamless, high-quality support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Serve as the escalation point&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for operational and workflow issues — providing timely guidance and resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and support process improvement&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;initiatives, including documentation, training design, and system enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop and deliver training&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for new hires and existing team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communicate with clarity&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;— keeping stakeholders informed on performance, escalations, and operational updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You Bring&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree from an accredited institution required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in operational or program management, preferably in education, healthcare, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience supporting multi-functional teams and implementing operational processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to translate data into action&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, Word, PowerPoint) and experience with CRM or workflow management systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master&#39;s degree from an accredited institution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Why Nightingale?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Nightingale, we believe in building a community where people grow, lead with transparency, and take ownership of outcomes that matter. You&#39;ll join a passionate team of collaborators who are serious about impact — and equally serious about supporting each other&#39;s success. This is a fully remote position with one annual in-person travel experience to connect with your team and community.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-

